Let us introduce you to <b>Stelly</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Stelly has been holding down the fort at <a href='/home/?user=stelly9'>73056-B Twilight Lane</a> in Golden Valley ever since July 21st this past summer. Stelly describes herself as being modest, which is a very difficult feat considering how many trophies she's won. Stelly likes to keep her eyes to the stars with her three junior astronomer's trophies. She's also great with numbers, so she shouldn't have any problem seeing she's been honored for Sudoku twice. <br><br>Shelly is also really interested in games, so it's no surprise that she splits most of her time between the playground and the amusement park. When she's relaxing, Shelly likes to hum along to quite a diverse music selection including the best from modern rock, oldies, and show tunes. <br><br>Movies may also be of high interest to Shelly, because she has her very own drive-in theater right in her backyard. You'll want to get to her private screenings early, because her stuffed animals have already taken half of the seating. If you're bringing food over for dinner before the flick you'll have no problem finding storage in one of the eight different refrigerators Shelly has in her kitchen.<br><br>Part of Shelly's backyard also happens to house treasure from the far reaches of the world. You'll wonder how she found time to discover dinosaur fossils, a totem pole, and an Egyptian sarcophagus. Maybe the hard part wasn't finding the time, but finding these rare objects. It's a skill only seasoned treasure hunters possess. <br><br>Wherever you happen to find Shelly, be sure to congratulate her and thank her for being such an outstanding citizen.<br></div>
